description:
File: rust/lichen-oscore/src/edhoc.rs:147-152

Issue: The code has several .expect() calls with comments saying they are INFALLIBLE:
    let hk = Hkdf::<Sha256>::from_prk(prk).expect("PRK is 32 bytes...");
    okm.resize(length, 0).expect("output Vec<u8, 32>...");
    hk.expand(&info, &mut okm).expect("requested length <= 32...");

While the comments explain why these cannot fail, using .expect() still generates panic code. For no_std embedded targets, this bloats the binary.

Idiomatic improvement:
1. Use const assertions or static_assert! macros where possible
2. Consider using unsafe { .unwrap_unchecked() } for truly infallible cases (with safety comment)
3. Or accept the .expect() with good comments (current approach is fine for non-size-critical builds)
